💻 Technical
Topic: Computer Basics
1️⃣ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

A computer is an electronic device that:

Accepts input

Processes data

Produces output

Basic components:

Input devices

CPU

Memory

Output devices

2️⃣ Basic Computer Components
🔹 Input Devices

Used to give data to computer.

Examples:

Keyboard

Mouse

Scanner

Microphone

🔹 Output Devices

Show results from computer.

Examples:

Monitor

Printer

Speaker

🔹 CPU (Central Processing Unit)

Known as the brain of computer.

Parts:

ALU → Arithmetic operations

CU → Controls operations

🔹 Memory Types

RAM → Temporary memory

ROM → Permanent memory

🔹 Software

Two types:

System software → Windows, Linux

Application software → MS Word, Excel

🧠 Quick Tricks (Railway Exams)

CPU = brain of computer

RAM = temporary memory

ROM = permanent memory

Input → processing → output cycle

